Class: PageRef A reference to a specific part of a document as indicated by a list of one or more page numbers, a range of page numbers, or a list of named destinations in the document (e.g. bookmarks). docs.text: Slot: whereClauses A list of one or more where clauses (selection criteria) to be combined or negated. URI: ars:whereClauses Applicable Classes Name Description Modifies Slot WhereClauseCompoundExpression A compound expression consisting of either two or more where clauses combined... no CompoundSetExpression A compound expression consisting of either two or more identified analysis se... yes CompoundGroupExpression A compound expression consisting of either two or more identified group combi... yes CompoundSubsetExpression A compound expression consisting of either two or more where clauses combined... yes Properties Range: WhereClause Multivalued: True Comments Each where clause may be defined as either a simple condition ([variable] [comparator] [value(s)]) or a compound expression that may combine additional simple conditions or compound expressions. Two or more where clauses should be specified when the logical operator is AND or OR. Only one where clause should be specfied when the logical operator is NOT. This where clause will usually be a compound expression.
